Parliament passed a law allowingstate-owned industrial companies to sell 49 pct of their sharesto staff and private investors, the official BSS news agencysaid.    Under the new law, passed yesterday, 51 pct of shares inthe affected companies will be held by the government, 34 pctby the public and 15 pct by staff. The law also allows workersto nominate a member to the board of directors if they buy atleast 12 pct of a company's shares.    Bangladesh has returned more than 500 industrial companiesto private ownership since March 1982. REUTER&#3;